---
import TerminalBlock from './TerminalBlock.astro';
---
<section id="quickstart">
  <h2>Quickstart</h2>
  <p>Install from npm, initialize your hub, then link all supported IDEs.</p>
  <TerminalBlock code={`$ npm install -g chain-hub\n$ chain init\n$ chain setup\n$ chain list`} />
  <p>
    By default your hub lives at <code>~/chain-hub</code> (visible in your home folder). You can override this with
    <code>CHAIN_HOME</code> when needed.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="up-to-date">
  <h2>CLI and hub updates</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>chain</code> command is installed from the <code>chain-hub</code> npm package.
    Update the CLI by running the same global install as for a fresh setup:
  </p>
  <TerminalBlock code={`$ npm install -g chain-hub\n$ chain --version`} />
  <p>
    After upgrading the CLI, run <code>chain init</code> so <code>CHAIN_HOME/core/</code> matches the bundled core in that release.
    Run <code>chain setup</code> again if release notes mention IDE symlink changes.
    For skills installed from the registry or GitHub bundles, use <code>chain update</code>.
  </p>
</section>
